The formation of inclusion complexes between HP-β-CD, Me-β-CD, and α-CD with HAL in aqueous solution was analyzed using the Job’s plot method. The difference between absorbance intensity with and without CD (ΔA) at 246 nm was determined using the mixtures of HAL:CD having different molar ratios (from 0 to 1) but keeping the total molar concentration of the components constant. The mixtures were prepared using equimolar solutions of HAL and CD. ΔA × R was plotted against R, where R is defined by the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
